		"description": "<p>Beginning at 9th level, you gain the ability to empower your @UUID[Compendium.a5e-bloody-heretics.bloody-heretics.Item.XuB01Vt0ev8WBOPt]{Sanguine Transference}, increasing the potency of your strikes. You gain the following empowerments, and can use this feature twice at no cost between long rests. Alternatively, you may expend one hit die to gain a use an Empowered Transference.</p>\n<h2>Blinding Transference</h2>\n<p>You focus your strikes to slash at your foe&rsquo;s eyes.The target makes a Constitution saving throw versus your maneuver DC. On a failure, the creature is blinded for 1 minute. The creature may repeat its saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on a success.</p>\n<h2>Lacerating Transference</h2>\n<p>You hack into your foe with surprising force and ferocity, aiming to maim more than kill efficiently. The target makes a Constitution saving throw. On a failure, that creature&rsquo;s wound begins to bleed profusely, and they take 1d6 ongoing bleed damage. The target continues to take this damage unless they use an action to staunch the bleeding. Creatures without blood (such as constructs and oozes) are unaffected.</p>\n<h2>Restraining Transference</h2>\n<p>Your strike reaches deep into your foe&rsquo;s very being as you attempt to lock their joints into place. The target makes a Constitution saving throw. On a failure, the creature is restrained. The target may repeat their saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on a success.</p>",
